The three-train terminal, a joint venture between QatarEnergy and ExxonMobil, is seeking authorization from the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) to run gas through more of train 1's equipment including the cold end, which is often one of the final steps before LNG production begins. The most traded May iron ore contract on China's Dalian Commodity Exchange (DCE), which ended the daytime trading 0.27% higher, was 750.5 yuan per metric ton ($109.47).
